This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to face swapping, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel attributes encoder and generator with adaptive attentional denormalization layers, which involves machine learning techniques and could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a heuristic error acknowledging refinement network for addressing facial occlusions, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
